
[1]radiancy

   RA'DIANCY, n. [L. radians, radio, to beam or shoot rays. See Radius and
   Ray.]

   Properly, brightness shooting in rays or beams; hence in general,
   brilliant or sparkling luster; vivid brightness; as the radiance of the
   sun.

   The Son girt with omnipotence, with radiance crown'd of majesty divine.
